commit.message:
Follow-up to c2d6278. NPE->ClosedChannelException for closed socket

If an attempt is made to use a closed socket, throw a
ClosedChannelException rather than a NullPointerException

Fix https://github.com/apache/tomcat/pull/187 Avoid NPE

Avoid a NullPointerException in the CrawlerSessionManagerValve if no
ROOT Context is deployed and a request does not map to any of the other
deployed Contexts.
Patch provided by Jop Zinkweg.

Fix https://bz.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=63913 Wrap NPEs

Wrap any NullPointerExceptions throw by the Inflater or Deflater used by
the PerMessageDeflate extension in an IOException so that the error can
be caught and handled by the WebSocket error handling mechanism.
Fix NPE reported by CI system
Do not throw NPE when MBean operation cannot be found.

Fix https://bz.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=64005 avoid NPE

Avoid the NPE when working with the URL for the root of a packed WAR
Fix possible NPE with excessive header size
Fix NPEs when looking for static methods
63706: Avoid NPE accessing https port with plaintext

Fix potential NPE in some embedding scenarios.

When embedding a Service directly and JNDI is enabled there is no Server
Port NPE prevention fix from NIO
NPE protection primarily for access log
Avoid non fatal NPEs with Tribes when JMX is not available
Avoid possible NPE on commit

Fix https://bz.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=63246

Fix a potential NullPointerException when calling
AsyncContext.dispatch()
Avoid possible NPE reported by Coverity scan
Fix rare potential NPE identified by Coverity Scan.
Avoid NPE when minimal Context defined in server.xml
Fix NPE when using with a default Tomcat configuration

Avoid other cases of NPEs on stop

As found in the CI logs.

Attempt to fix APR flush

Fix NPE I saw in maintain. Do a CI run to see the results (will still be
disabled afterwards since the performance is obviously worse).

The closed channels need to be immutable so override a few more methods

Avoiding a NPE in NioBlockignSelector is not possible however and
getting there is wasteful, so filter out read as well. In theory ==
CLOSED_NIO_CHANNEL would be enough but use instanceof for now.

Protect from NPE in testcase.
